Note: SECTION 3: Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Returns the network identifier.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_network" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(a, ADDR_OFF_NETWORK)
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the address byte pointer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public material.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_bytes" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(a, ADDR_OFF_BYTES_PTR)
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the address byte length.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Reads qword at offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_byte_length" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_qword(a, ADDR_OFF_BYTES_LEN)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 4: Ethereum
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct an Ethereum Address from a 40-character hex string. The
optional "0x" prefix is accepted and stripped. EIP-55 mixed-case
checksum is validated: every uppercase hex digit at position i must
correspond to a high nibble of keccak256(lowercase_address)[i/2], or
the input is rejected.

Accepts all-lowercase or all-uppercase inputs (which have no checksum
information by construction), and accepts EIP-55-correct mixed-case.
Rejects mixed-case strings whose case-pattern does NOT match the
EIP-55 derivation. This prevents the common typo-induced address
substitution.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Strip "0x" prefix if present.
  2. Require length == 40.
  3. Decode hex into 20-byte address.
  4. Determine if input is all-lower, all-upper, or mixed.
  5. If mixed: compute keccak256(lower_hex_chars) and re-derive the
     EIP-55 case pattern; compare against input. Reject on mismatch.
  6. Allocate Address with NETWORK_ETHEREUM and 20-byte payload.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(n) for parse + one keccak256(40 bytes).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The EIP-55 check is the protection against single-character typos in
Ethereum addresses (a 4-bit-per-char checksum has expected failure
probability ~1/2 per typo on average). This proc REJECTS mixed-case
inputs that fail the check, which is the safe default; downstream code
must NOT silently accept such inputs.

References:
- EIP-55: Mixed-case checksum address encoding for Ethereum addresses
  (Hawkins 2016).
- Ethereum Yellow Paper section 4.1.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_ethereum_from_hex" takes arena as Integer, hex_str as Integer, hex_length as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hex_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Strip 0x prefix if present.
    Let start_off be 0
    Let raw_len be hex_length
    If hex_length is greater than or equal to 2:
        Let p0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(hex_str, 0)
        Let p1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(hex_str, 1)
        If p0 is equal to 48:
            If p1 is equal to 120:
                Set start_off to 2
                Set raw_len to raw_len minus 2
            End If
            If p1 is equal to 88:
                Set start_off to 2
                Set raw_len to raw_len minus 2
            End If
        End If
    End If

    If raw_len is not equal to 40:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Decode 20 raw bytes and classify case.
    Let addr_bytes be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 20)
    If addr_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let has_upper be 0
    Let has_lower be 0
    Let pi be 0
    While pi is less than 20:
        Let hi_c be Memory.memory_get_byte(hex_str, start_off plus (pi multiplied by 2))
        Let lo_c be Memory.memory_get_byte(hex_str, (start_off plus (pi multiplied by 2)) plus 1)
        Let hi_v be Char.hex_digit_value(hi_c)
        Let lo_v be Char.hex_digit_value(lo_c)
        If hi_v is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        If lo_v is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: Track case for a-f / A-F to decide EIP-55 check requirement.
        If hi_c is greater than or equal to 65:
            If hi_c is less than or equal to 70:
                Set has_upper to 1
            End If
        End If
        If hi_c is greater than or equal to 97:
            If hi_c is less than or equal to 102:
                Set has_lower to 1
            End If
        End If
        If lo_c is greater than or equal to 65:
            If lo_c is less than or equal to 70:
                Set has_upper to 1
            End If
        End If
        If lo_c is greater than or equal to 97:
            If lo_c is less than or equal to 102:
                Set has_lower to 1
            End If
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(addr_bytes, pi, (hi_v multiplied by 16) plus lo_v)
        Set pi to pi plus 1
    End While

    Note: If both upper and lower hex letters present, validate EIP-55.
    If has_upper is equal to 1:
        If has_lower is equal to 1:
            Let lower_hex be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 40)
            If lower_hex is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let li be 0
            While li is less than 40:
                Let c be Memory.memory_get_byte(hex_str, start_off plus li)
                If c is greater than or equal to 65:
                    If c is less than or equal to 70:
                        Set c to c plus 32
                    End If
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_byte(lower_hex, li, c)
                Set li to li plus 1
            End While
            Let chk_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
            If chk_buf is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let kr be addr_keccak256(arena, lower_hex, 40, chk_buf)
            If kr is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Note: For each i in 0..39: high nibble of chk_buf[i/2]
            Note: (if i even) or low nibble (if i odd) >= 8 means the hex
            Note: character at position i must be uppercase (A-F), else
            Note: lowercase. Letters only; digits ignored.
            Let vi be 0
            While vi is less than 40:
                Let raw_c be Memory.memory_get_byte(hex_str, start_off plus vi)
                Let is_letter be 0
                If raw_c is greater than or equal to 65:
                    If raw_c is less than or equal to 70:
                        Set is_letter to 1
                    End If
                End If
                If raw_c is greater than or equal to 97:
                    If raw_c is less than or equal to 102:
                        Set is_letter to 1
                    End If
                End If
                If is_letter is equal to 1:
                    Let byte_idx be vi divided by 2
                    Let nib_b be Memory.memory_get_byte(chk_buf, byte_idx)
                    Let nibble be 0
                    If (vi modulo by 2) is equal to 0:
                        Set nibble to nib_b divided by 16
                    Otherwise:
                        Set nibble to nib_b modulo by 16
                    End If
                    Let expect_upper be 0
                    If nibble is greater than or equal to 8:
                        Set expect_upper to 1
                    End If
                    Let actual_upper be 0
                    If raw_c is less than or equal to 70:
                        Set actual_upper to 1
                    End If
                    If actual_upper is not equal to expect_upper:
                        Return 0
                    End If
                End If
                Set vi to vi plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If

    Return address_create(arena, NETWORK_ETHEREUM, addr_bytes, 20)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 5: Bitcoin
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a Bitcoin address from a Base58Check string. The format is:
  base58( version_byte || payload || checksum_4 )
where checksum_4 = first 4 bytes of sha256(sha256(version_byte || payload)).

Valid input lengths after Base58 decoding:
  25 bytes total: 1 version + 20 payload + 4 checksum (P2PKH / P2SH).
  37 bytes total: 1 version + 32 payload + 4 checksum (variant).
The version byte distinguishes mainnet / testnet / P2SH / etc.

The decoded payload (without version or checksum) is stored as the
address bytes; the version byte is stored at offset[0] of the buffer
to preserve mainnet/testnet distinguishability while still using
a single NETWORK_BITCOIN tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Validate input.
  2. Base58-decode into 25-byte buffer.
  3. Split into version|payload|checksum.
  4. Verify checksum: sha256(sha256(version||payload))[0..4] == checksum.
  5. Allocate Address bytes = version || payload (21 bytes).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Two SHA-256 invocations on 21-byte input plus one Base58 decode.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Checksum verification catches single-character typos with probability
1 - 2^-32 ~ 100%. Rejecting on checksum failure is mandatory; a silent
default would route funds to the wrong address.

References:
- Bitcoin Wiki: Base58Check encoding.
- BIP-13: Pay-to-Script-Hash (P2SH) base58 encoding.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_bitcoin_from_base58" takes arena as Integer, b58_str as Integer, b58_length as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b58_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b58_length is less than 26:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b58_length is greater than 60:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate a generous decode buffer. Base58 decode of a 60-char
    Note: string is at most 60 bytes (well above the 25-byte target).
    Let decode_cap be b58_length
    Let decoded be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, decode_cap)
    If decoded is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dec_len be addr_base58_decode(b58_str, b58_length, decoded, decode_cap)
    If dec_len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If dec_len is less than 25:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Split: version(1) + payload(dec_len-5) + checksum(4).
    Let payload_offset be 0
    Let payload_len be dec_len minus 4
    Let checksum_offset be payload_len

    Note: Compute sha256(sha256(version || payload)).
    Let h1 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    If h1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let h2 be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    If h2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let r1 be Sha2.sha256_hash(arena, decoded plus payload_offset, payload_len, h1)
    If r1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let r2 be Sha2.sha256_hash(arena, h1, 32, h2)
    If r2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Compare h2[0..4] to checksum[0..4] in constant time.
    Let chk_match be Secure.constant_time_compare(h2, decoded plus checksum_offset, 4)
    If chk_match is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return address_create(arena, NETWORK_BITCOIN, decoded, payload_len)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 6: Solana
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Solana addresses are 32-byte Ed25519 public keys encoded in Base58
(no checksum byte). The encoding is between 32 and 44 characters
typically (most public keys produce 44 chars; addresses starting with
many leading-zero bytes shrink).

This proc decodes Base58 and validates the result is exactly 32 bytes.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Validate input length is 32..44.
  2. Base58-decode into 32-byte target.
  3. Validate decoded length is exactly 32.
  4. Allocate Address with NETWORK_SOLANA.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(input chars) Base58 decode.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Solana addresses have no checksum (the format relies on rejecting
non-Ed25519-key addresses at signature verification time). The
length validation is the only structural check available.

For destinations that you have not received via a trusted channel,
DO NOT rely on Solana address validation alone; require a recent
signed message from the holder as proof of control.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_solana_from_base58" takes arena as Integer, b58_str as Integer, b58_length as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b58_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b58_length is less than 32:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b58_length is greater than 44:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let decode_cap be 48
    Let decoded be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, decode_cap)
    If decoded is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dec_len be addr_base58_decode(b58_str, b58_length, decoded, decode_cap)
    If dec_len is not equal to 32:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return address_create(arena, NETWORK_SOLANA, decoded, 32)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 7: Cosmos (Bech32)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Bech32 (BIP-173) encodes a binary string with a human-readable prefix
(HRP) and a 6-character checksum. The format is:
  hrp || "1" || data_chars || checksum
where:
  hrp        : lowercase ASCII letters
  data_chars : Base32-encoded payload using the alphabet
               "qpzry9x8gf2tvdw0s3jn54khce6mua7l"
  checksum   : 6 Bech32 characters computed via polymod over GF(2^5).

Validation requires:
  - Last separator '1' present.
  - hrp non-empty, lowercase letters only.
  - data chars from the Bech32 alphabet only.
  - checksum polymod equals BECH32_CONST (1 for original Bech32,
    0x2bc830a3 for Bech32m).

This proc supports both Bech32 (BIP-173) and Bech32m (BIP-350); the
constant is chosen by the caller via a separate bech32m flag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Find last '1' in input; everything before is HRP, after is data.
  2. Validate HRP is non-empty, all chars in 'a'..'z'.
  3. Decode data chars to 5-bit values.
  4. Compute polymod over expanded HRP || data and verify.
  5. Convert data[0..len-6] from 5-bit groups to 8-bit bytes.
  6. Allocate Address with NETWORK_COSMOS and the byte payload.
     Also stores the original encoded string for round-trip.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(n) parse + O(n) polymod.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The polymod checksum detects up to 4 character substitutions with
probability ~1 - 2^-30, far stronger than Base58Check's 4-byte sha2
prefix. Mandatory check.

References:
- BIP-173: Base32 address format (Bech32).
- BIP-350: Bech32m for v1+ witness addresses.
- Cosmos SDK address spec: bech32 with HRP per chain.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_cosmos_from_bech32" takes arena as Integer, bech_str as Integer, bech_length as Integer returns Integer:
    Return address_cosmos_from_bech32_variant(arena, bech_str, bech_length, 0)
End Process

@Reasoning
Bech32 decoder with explicit variant selection: variant=0 -> Bech32
(original), variant=1 -> Bech32m. Both variants share parsing; only
the polymod constant differs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Same as above; selects BECH32_CONST = 1 or 0x2bc830a3.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Same as the Bech32 path.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Same as the Bech32 path.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_cosmos_from_bech32_variant" takes arena as Integer, bech_str as Integer, bech_length as Integer, variant as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If bech_str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If bech_length is less than 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    If bech_length is greater than 90:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Find last '1' separator (ASCII 49).
    Let sep_idx be 0 minus 1
    Let scan_i be bech_length minus 1
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        Let cs be Memory.memory_get_byte(bech_str, scan_i)
        If cs is equal to 49:
            Set sep_idx to scan_i
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            If scan_i is equal to 0:
                Set scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Set scan_i to scan_i minus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    If sep_idx is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let data_count be (bech_length minus sep_idx) minus 1
    If data_count is less than 6:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Decode data chars into 5-bit values; check HRP chars are lowercase.
    Let data_vals be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, data_count)
    If data_vals is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hi be 0
    While hi is less than sep_idx:
        Let hc be Memory.memory_get_byte(bech_str, hi)
        If hc is less than 97:
            Return 0
        End If
        If hc is greater than 122:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set hi to hi plus 1
    End While
    Let di be 0
    While di is less than data_count:
        Let dc be Memory.memory_get_byte(bech_str, (sep_idx plus 1) plus di)
        Let dv be addr_bech32_char_value(dc)
        If dv is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(data_vals, di, dv)
        Set di to di plus 1
    End While

    Note: Compute polymod over expanded HRP || data and verify.
    Let polymod be addr_bech32_verify_checksum(bech_str, sep_idx, data_vals, data_count)
    Let expected be 1
    If variant is equal to 1:
        Set expected to 734539683
    End If
    Note: 0x2bc830a3 = 734539683.
    If polymod is not equal to expected:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Convert data[0..count-6] from 5-bit to 8-bit; output is the byte payload.
    Let payload_5bit_count be data_count minus 6
    Let max_8bit_len be (payload_5bit_count multiplied by 5) divided by 8
    If max_8bit_len is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let payload_bytes be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, max_8bit_len plus 1)
    If payload_bytes is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let actual_byte_len be addr_bech32_convert_bits(data_vals, payload_5bit_count, 5, payload_bytes, max_8bit_len plus 1, 8, 0)
    If actual_byte_len is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build the Address. Network is NETWORK_COSMOS for any bech32-style.
    Note: For consumers needing the HRP (chain prefix), they can re-derive it
    Note: from the encoded string we save below.
    Let a be address_create(arena, NETWORK_COSMOS, payload_bytes, actual_byte_len)
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Store the original encoded string for round-trip.
    Let enc_copy be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, bech_length)
    If enc_copy is equal to 0:
        Return a
    End If
    Memory.memory_copy(enc_copy, bech_str, bech_length)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(a, ADDR_OFF_ENCODED_PTR, enc_copy)
    Memory.memory_set_qword(a, ADDR_OFF_ENCODED_LEN, bech_length)
    Return a
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the 5-bit value 0..31 for a Bech32 character (lowercase only),
or -1 for invalid. The Bech32 alphabet is:
  "qpzry9x8gf2tvdw0s3jn54khce6mua7l"
which is intentionally chosen to detect single-character substitutions
in BCH-style polymod (BIP-173 section "Choice of character set").
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Direct enumeration of the 32-character alphabet.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Decoder is strict (lowercase only) per BIP-173.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "addr_bech32_char_value" takes c as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: 'q'=113 -> 0, 'p'=112 -> 1, 'z'=122 -> 2, ...
    If c is equal to 113:
        Return 0
    End If
    If c is equal to 112:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 122:
        Return 2
    End If
    If c is equal to 114:
        Return 3
    End If
    If c is equal to 121:
        Return 4
    End If
    If c is equal to 57:
        Return 5
    End If
    If c is equal to 120:
        Return 6
    End If
    If c is equal to 56:
        Return 7
    End If
    If c is equal to 103:
        Return 8
    End If
    If c is equal to 102:
        Return 9
    End If
    If c is equal to 50:
        Return 10
    End If
    If c is equal to 116:
        Return 11
    End If
    If c is equal to 118:
        Return 12
    End If
    If c is equal to 100:
        Return 13
    End If
    If c is equal to 119:
        Return 14
    End If
    If c is equal to 48:
        Return 15
    End If
    If c is equal to 115:
        Return 16
    End If
    If c is equal to 51:
        Return 17
    End If
    If c is equal to 106:
        Return 18
    End If
    If c is equal to 110:
        Return 19
    End If
    If c is equal to 53:
        Return 20
    End If
    If c is equal to 52:
        Return 21
    End If
    If c is equal to 107:
        Return 22
    End If
    If c is equal to 104:
        Return 23
    End If
    If c is equal to 99:
        Return 24
    End If
    If c is equal to 101:
        Return 25
    End If
    If c is equal to 54:
        Return 26
    End If
    If c is equal to 109:
        Return 27
    End If
    If c is equal to 117:
        Return 28
    End If
    If c is equal to 97:
        Return 29
    End If
    If c is equal to 55:
        Return 30
    End If
    If c is equal to 108:
        Return 31
    End If
    Return 0 minus 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Compute the BCH polymod of HRP-expansion || data, per BIP-173. The
polymod is iterated as:
  c = 1
  for v in expanded:
      b = c >> 25
      c = ((c & 0x1ffffff) << 5) ^ v
      for i in 0..4:
          c ^= GEN[i] if (b >> i) & 1
where GEN = [0x3b6a57b2, 0x26508e6d, 0x1ea119fa, 0x3d4233dd, 0x2a1462b3].

HRP expansion per BIP-173:
  expanded = [c >> 5 for c in hrp] + [0] + [c & 31 for c in hrp]

The function returns the resulting polymod value c.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Builds the expanded sequence on the fly without materializing into a
buffer (just iterates the three sub-ranges). Constants are from
BIP-173 section "Bech32".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(hrp_len + data_len). One iteration over each character.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure polynomial computation; no secret-dependent paths.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "addr_bech32_verify_checksum" takes hrp_str as Integer, hrp_len as Integer, data_vals as Integer, data_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let c be 1
    Note: hrp high nibbles.
    Let hi be 0
    While hi is less than hrp_len:
        Let cc be Memory.memory_get_byte(hrp_str, hi)
        Let v be cc divided by 32
        Set c to addr_bech32_polymod_step(c, v)
        Set hi to hi plus 1
    End While
    Note: separator 0.
    Set c to addr_bech32_polymod_step(c, 0)
    Note: hrp low nibbles.
    Let li be 0
    While li is less than hrp_len:
        Let cc2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(hrp_str, li)
        Let v2 be cc2 modulo by 32
        Set c to addr_bech32_polymod_step(c, v2)
        Set li to li plus 1
    End While
    Note: data values.
    Let di be 0
    While di is less than data_len:
        Let dv be Memory.memory_get_byte(data_vals, di)
        Set c to addr_bech32_polymod_step(c, dv)
        Set di to di plus 1
    End While
    Return c
End Process

@Reasoning
Single polymod step. Implements one iteration of the BCH polymod
recurrence using the GF(2^5) generator constants from BIP-173.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
b = c >> 25, c = ((c & 0x1ffffff) << 5) xor v, then conditionally xor
each of GEN[0..4] = {0x3b6a57b2, 0x26508e6d, 0x1ea119fa, 0x3d4233dd,
0x2a1462b3} if the corresponding bit of b is set.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1) — five conditional xors per step.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure arithmetic.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "addr_bech32_polymod_step" takes c as Integer, v as Integer returns Integer:
    Let b be c divided by 33554432
    Note: 33554432 = 2^25.
    Let masked be c modulo by 33554432
    Let shifted be masked multiplied by 32
    Let new_c be shifted bitwise_xor v
    Note: GEN constants per BIP-173:
    Note: 0x3b6a57b2 = 996825010
    Note: 0x26508e6d = 642813757
    Note: 0x1ea119fa = 513874426
    Note: 0x3d4233dd = 1027748829
    Note: 0x2a1462b3 = 705979059
    If (b bitwise_and 1) is not equal to 0:
        Set new_c to new_c bitwise_xor 996825010
    End If
    If (b bitwise_and 2) is not equal to 0:
        Set new_c to new_c bitwise_xor 642813757
    End If
    If (b bitwise_and 4) is not equal to 0:
        Set new_c to new_c bitwise_xor 513874426
    End If
    If (b bitwise_and 8) is not equal to 0:
        Set new_c to new_c bitwise_xor 1027748829
    End If
    If (b bitwise_and 16) is not equal to 0:
        Set new_c to new_c bitwise_xor 705979059
    End If
    Return new_c
End Process

@Reasoning
Convert a sequence of from_bits-bit values to to_bits-bit values per
BIP-173 convertbits routine. Handles the leftover-bit boundary by
optionally requiring (pad=1) trailing zero bits or rejecting (pad=0).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Standard accumulator: walk input, shift accumulator left by from_bits,
or in the next input, emit (acc >> excess) when accumulator holds
to_bits or more.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(n) where n is the input count.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Pure arithmetic; rejects non-padded input when pad=0 (the canonical
decode path).
@End Security_Scope
Process called "addr_bech32_convert_bits" takes input_buf as Integer, input_count as Integer, from_bits as Integer, out_buf as Integer, out_capacity as Integer, to_bits as Integer, pad as Integer returns Integer:
    Let acc be 0
    Let bits be 0
    Let written be 0
    Let max_v be 1
    Let mk_i be 0
    While mk_i is less than to_bits:
        Set max_v to max_v multiplied by 2
        Set mk_i to mk_i plus 1
    End While
    Set max_v to max_v minus 1

    Let in_mask be 1
    Let im_i be 0
    While im_i is less than from_bits:
        Set in_mask to in_mask multiplied by 2
        Set im_i to im_i plus 1
    End While
    Set in_mask to in_mask minus 1

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than input_count:
        Let v be Memory.memory_get_byte(input_buf, i)
        If v is greater than in_mask:
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: acc = (acc << from_bits) | v
        Let shift_factor be 1
        Let sf_i be 0
        While sf_i is less than from_bits:
            Set shift_factor to shift_factor multiplied by 2
            Set sf_i to sf_i plus 1
        End While
        Set acc to (acc multiplied by shift_factor) bitwise_or v
        Set bits to bits plus from_bits
        While bits is greater than or equal to to_bits:
            Set bits to bits minus to_bits
            Let div_factor be 1
            Let df_i be 0
            While df_i is less than bits:
                Set div_factor to div_factor multiplied by 2
                Set df_i to df_i plus 1
            End While
            Let chunk be (acc divided by div_factor) bitwise_and max_v
            If written is greater than or equal to out_capacity:
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buf, written, chunk)
            Set written to written plus 1
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If pad is equal to 1:
        If bits is greater than 0:
            Let div_factor2 be 1
            Let df2_i be 0
            Let shift_left be to_bits minus bits
            While df2_i is less than shift_left:
                Set div_factor2 to div_factor2 multiplied by 2
                Set df2_i to df2_i plus 1
            End While
            Let final_chunk be (acc multiplied by div_factor2) bitwise_and max_v
            If written is greater than or equal to out_capacity:
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buf, written, final_chunk)
            Set written to written plus 1
        End If
    Otherwise:
        Note: No-pad mode: leftover bits must be zero.
        If bits is greater than 0:
            Let trail_mask be 1
            Let tm_i be 0
            While tm_i is less than bits:
                Set trail_mask to trail_mask multiplied by 2
                Set tm_i to tm_i plus 1
            End While
            Set trail_mask to trail_mask minus 1
            Let trail_bits be acc bitwise_and trail_mask
            If trail_bits is not equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Return written
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 8: Equality
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Two addresses are equal iff they share network AND byte payload (constant-
time compare on bytes). Cross-network comparison ALWAYS returns 0.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Algorithm/length checks then constant_time_compare.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Constant-time on byte content (treats address bytes as if they were
secrets, conservatively). Network-tag and length checks are early-exit
because they are public.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "address_equal" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let na be address_network(a)
    Let nb be address_network(b)
    If na is not equal to nb:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let la be address_byte_length(a)
    Let lb be address_byte_length(b)
    If la is not equal to lb:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ba be address_bytes(a)
    Let bb be address_bytes(b)
    Return Secure.constant_time_compare(ba, bb, la)
End Process
